{"cursor":"27451","size":15,"audio":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/40/It-Benevento.ogg"],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{{Infobox Italian comune\n| name = Benevento official_name = Comune di Benevento native_name = image_flag\n| = Flag of Benevento.svg image_skyline = Benevento-Panorama da Via del\n| Pomerio.jpg imagesize = image_alt = image_caption = image_shield =Benevento-\n| Stemma (1).png shield_alt = image_map = Map - IT - Benevento - Benevento.svg\n| map_alt = map_caption = Benevento within the Province of Benevento\n| pushpin_label_position = pushpin_map_alt = latd = 41 |latm = 08 |lats = |latNS\n| = N longd = 14 |longm = 47 |longs = |longEW = E coordinates_type =\n| coordinates_display = coordinates_footnotes = region = Campania province =\n| Benevento (BN) frazioni = see list mayor_party = mayor = Fausto Pepe\n| area_footnotes = area_total_km2 = 129 population_footnotes = population_total\n| = 61700 population_as_of = 30 June 2011 pop_density_footnotes =\n| population_demonym = Beneventani elevation_footnotes = elevation_m = 135 twin1\n| = twin1_country = saint = St. Bartholomew day = August 24 postal_code = 82100\n| area_code = 0824 website = footnotes =\n}} mountain range]]\n\n'Benevento' is a city and [[comune]] of Campania, Italy, capital of the province\nof Benevento, northeast of Naples. It is situated on a hill above sea-level at\nthe confluence of the Calore Irpino (or Beneventano) and the Sabato. It is also\nthe seat of a Roman Catholic archbishop.\n\nBenevento occupies the site of the ancient 'Beneventum', originally 'Maleventum'\nor still earlier Maloenton. The \"-vent\" portion of the name probably refers to a\nmarket-place and is a common element in ancient place names. E. McClure,\nBritish Place-Names in their Historical Settings, London (1910), pp. 32-34\nThe Romans theorized that it meant \"the site of bad events\", from Mal(um) +\neventum. In the imperial period it was supposed to have been founded by Diomedes\nafter the Trojan War.\n\nDue to its artistic and cultural significance, the Santa Sofia's Church in\nBenevento has been recently declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site as part of\na group of seven inscribed as Longobards in Italy. Places of the power (568-\n774 A.D.).\n","linknr":578,"url":"Benevento","recorded":1375082772,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Benevento&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Benevento&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/B%C3%A9n%C3%A9vent_(disambiguation)","/wiki/Comune","/wiki/File:Benevento-Panorama_da_Via_del_Pomerio.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Benevento-Panorama_da_Via_del_Pomerio.jpg/250px-Benevento-Panorama_da_Via_del_Pomerio.jpg","/wiki/File:Flag_of_Benevento.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Flag_of_Benevento.svg/100px-Flag_of_Benevento.svg.png","/wiki/File:Benevento-Stemma_(1).png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b0/Benevento-Stemma_%281%29.png/100px-Benevento-Stemma_%281%29.png","/wiki/File:Map_-_IT_-_Benevento_-_Benevento.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Map_-_IT_-_Benevento_-_Benevento.svg/250px-Map_-_IT_-_Benevento_-_Benevento.svg.png","/wiki/File:Italy_provincial_location_map.sv